{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/learning-php/part2/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Konnor's Blog","author":"Konnor Rogers"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"c90be014-9e67-53b3-9c8d-7d44e0d7de60","excerpt":"Part 2 Laracasts main site\nLaracasts - PHP for beginners Chapters Chapter 2 - Install a code editor\nChapter 3 - Variables\nChapter 4 - PHP and HTML\nChapter…","html":"<h1>Part 2</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://laracasts.com\">Laracasts main site</a><br>\n<a href=\"https://laracasts.com/series/php-for-beginners\">Laracasts - PHP for beginners</a></p>\n<h2>Chapters</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://laracasts.com/series/php-for-beginners/episodes/2\">Chapter 2 - Install a code editor</a><br>\n<a href=\"https://laracasts.com/series/php-for-beginners/episodes/3\">Chapter 3 - Variables</a><br>\n<a href=\"https://laracasts.com/series/php-for-beginners/episodes/4\">Chapter 4 - PHP and HTML</a><br>\n<a href=\"https://laracasts.com/series/php-for-beginners/episodes/5\">Chapter 5 - Seperation of PHP logic</a></p>\n<h2>Hello World</h2>\n<p>Are you really learning a new program if you don’t create a simple hello world?</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container customButtonContainerClass\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"60206854510159790000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied to clipboard!\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"5000\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`// hello-world.php\n<?php\n\necho 'Hello World';`, `60206854510159790000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy to clipboard\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"php\"><pre class=\"language-php\"><code class=\"language-php\">// hello-world.php\n<span class=\"token php language-php\"><span class=\"token delimiter important\">&lt;?php</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">echo</span> <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'Hello World'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></span></code></pre></div>\n<br>\n<p>In a terminal run:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container customButtonContainerClass\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"24204604437375533000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied to clipboard!\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"5000\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`php hello-world.php`, `24204604437375533000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy to clipboard\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">php hello-world.php</code></pre></div>\n<br>\n<p>Should echo ‘Hello World’ to the command line.\n<strong>Note: </strong>Also of note, when in a plain php file, <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;?php</code> without the closing <code class=\"language-text\">?&gt;</code> is best\npractice due to parsing errors if you add extra lines after <code class=\"language-text\">?&gt;</code></p>\n<p>Easy win after the nightmare install process.</p>\n<h2>Variables</h2>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container customButtonContainerClass\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"27875529471896596000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied to clipboard!\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"5000\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`// index.php\n<?php\n\n\\$name = 'Konnor Rogers';\n\n// Concats \\$name onto 'Hello'\necho 'Hello' . \\$name;\n\n// Or\necho &quot;Hello {\\$name}&quot;;`, `27875529471896596000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy to clipboard\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"php\"><pre class=\"language-php\"><code class=\"language-php\">// index.php\n<span class=\"token php language-php\"><span class=\"token delimiter important\">&lt;?php</span>\n\n<span class=\"token variable\">$name</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'Konnor Rogers'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Concats $name onto 'Hello'</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">echo</span> <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'Hello'</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$name</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Or</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">echo</span> <span class=\"token double-quoted-string string\">\"Hello <span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token variable\">$name</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span>\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></span></code></pre></div>\n<br>\n<h2>HTML + PHP</h2>\n<p>Pulling in parameters</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container customButtonContainerClass\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"40110166605124740000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied to clipboard!\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"5000\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`// index.php\n<?php\n\n// pulls in the 'name' parameter\n\\$name = htmlspecialchars(\\$_GET['name']);\n\necho &quot;Hello, &quot; . \\$name;\n// localhost:8888/?name=konnor #=> Hello, Konnor`, `40110166605124740000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy to clipboard\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"php\"><pre class=\"language-php\"><code class=\"language-php\">// index.php\n<span class=\"token php language-php\"><span class=\"token delimiter important\">&lt;?php</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// pulls in the 'name' parameter</span>\n<span class=\"token variable\">$name</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">htmlspecialchars</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$_GET</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'name'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">echo</span> <span class=\"token double-quoted-string string\">\"Hello, \"</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$name</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// localhost:8888/?name=konnor #=> Hello, Konnor</span></span></code></pre></div>\n<br>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">htmlspecialchars();</code> Will convert special characters as the name suggests so\npeople cannot inject malicious links, scripts, etc</p>\n<h2>Seperating php logic</h2>\n<p>In a small low level MVC framework, this is a microcosm of a view.\nindex.view.php is essentially a template to be rendered, and index.php provides\nany necessary variables to be rendered. For example: <br>\n<code class=\"language-text\">$greeting</code> may be the result of a database call. You want that to be done server\nside without concern for the actual way it is being rendered.</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container customButtonContainerClass\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"4322414881651881500\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied to clipboard!\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"5000\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`// index.php\n<?php\n\n\\$greeting = 'Hello World';\n\n// pulls in the view defined below\nrequire 'index.view.php';\n// Optionally, you can use: include 'index.view.php';\n// Read the note below about the difference`, `4322414881651881500`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy to clipboard\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"php\"><pre class=\"language-php\"><code class=\"language-php\">// index.php\n<span class=\"token php language-php\"><span class=\"token delimiter important\">&lt;?php</span>\n\n<span class=\"token variable\">$greeting</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'Hello World'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// pulls in the view defined below</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">require</span> <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'index.view.php'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Optionally, you can use: include 'index.view.php';</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Read the note below about the difference</span></span></code></pre></div>\n<br>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong> After perusing some documentation, <code class=\"language-text\">include</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">require</code>\ndo essentially the same thing. They pull in variables and other data @ the level\nit is called. The only difference is the following:<br>\n<code class=\"language-text\">include</code> <em>will not cause</em> a compilation error if the file does not exist\nor is unreadable. It will only send a compilation warning.<br>\n<code class=\"language-text\">require</code> <em>will cause</em> a compilation error if the file does not exist or is unreadable</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container customButtonContainerClass\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"15100771026210701000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied to clipboard!\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"5000\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`// index.view.php\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=&quot;en&quot;>\n  <meta charset=&quot;UTF-8&quot;>\n  <title>Document</title>\n  <style>\n    header {\n      background: #e3e3e3;\n      padding: 2rem;\n      text-align: center;\n    }\n  </style>\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    <header>\n      <h1><?= \\$greeting; ?></h1>\n    </header>\n  </body>\n</html>`, `15100771026210701000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy to clipboard\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"php\"><pre class=\"language-php\"><code class=\"language-php\">// index.view.php\n<span class=\"token doctype\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>html</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">lang</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>en<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>meta</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">charset</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>UTF-8<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>title</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Document<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>title</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>style</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token style\"><span class=\"token language-css\">\n    <span class=\"token selector\">header</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">background</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> #e3e3e3<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">padding</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 2rem<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">text-align</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> center<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  </span></span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>style</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>head</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>body</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>header</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n      <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token php language-php\"><span class=\"token delimiter important\">&lt;?=</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$greeting</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token delimiter important\">?></span></span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>header</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>body</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>html</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre></div>\n<br>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">&lt;?= ?&gt; is the same as &lt;?php echo &quot;string&quot; ?&gt;</code></p>\n<h2>Links</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://github.com/ParamagicDev/php-for-beginners\">Follow along with my repo</a></strong><br>\n<a href=\"https://laracasts.com\">Laracasts main site</a><br>\n<a href=\"https://laracasts.com/series/php-for-beginners\">PHP for beginners</a><br></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Learning PHP - Part 2 - Lets get coding!","date":"August 18, 2019","description":"Learn php with me! Part 2"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/learning-php/part2/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/learning-php/part1/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Learning PHP - Part 1 - Lets Compile PHP!"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/learning-php/part3/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Learning PHP - Part 3 - Arrays, Arrays, and more Arrays"}}}}}